Testament of Youth is a powerful story of love, war and remembrance,
based on the First World War memoir by Vera Brittain, which has become
the classic testimony of that war from a woman's point of view. A searing
journey from youthful hopes and dreams to the edge of despair and back
again, it's a film about young love, the futility of war and how to make
sense of the darkest times.
